rch on religious spatialities, cosmologies, and ideas of wild nature and brings new understanding of the role of religion in human interaction with ‘the world’.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCosmologyxReligious aspects. 0aNaturexReligious aspects. 0aSacred space. 0aWilderness areasxReligious aspects. 4aKosmologie. 4aNatur. 4aReligion. 4aRäumlichkeit. 4aWildnis. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aCosmology.  aNature.  aReligion.  aSpatiality.  aWilderness.1 aBremmer, Jan N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEndsjø, Dag Øistein, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeldt, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeldt, Laura, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGilhus, Ingvild Sælid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarvey, Graham, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffmann, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHornborg, Anne-Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPedersen, Morten Axel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQvortrup Fibiger, Marianne C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchjødt, Jens Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSegal, Robert A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaylor, Bron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (E